node.text:
Here’s a little pregnancy update for you guys🤗
I’m 34 weeks pregnant now, baby bump is getting so heavy 😱 I still can’t believe it every time I look at myself, how amazing our bodies are for what they are able to do, and the appreciation I have for my body now is just unreal! 

I’ve gained 18 pounds so far, doctor says baby weights around 5 😍 

I have worked out through each trimester (not crazy, mostly light home workouts) Swimming a lot, Walking a lot, eating healthy, trying to avoid junk food and sugar — of course not because I’m worried about my extra pounds, cellulite or snapping back afterwards, but to keep myself and baby active and healthy🧘🏻‍♀️ 
This last month for sure feels the most difficult  and challenging🥵 Baby’s growing every single day, and it feels more and more uncomfortable to do simple things😂
But in general my experience with pregnancy has been incredible and I’m feeling beyond exited and happy to meet my little baby and begin the next chapter of our life together 🥰

👙 Bikini from @nass_shop_
